<typeStatus box="[584,632,1685,1711]" pageId="3" pageNumber="252">type</typeStatus>
locality.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1612,1927]" pageId="3" pageNumber="252">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,357,1720,1746]" pageId="3" pageNumber="252">Observations:</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hustedt) Lange-Bertalot &amp; Metzeltin (1996: 64)" authorityName="Lange-Bertalot &amp; Metzeltin" authorityPageNumber="64" authorityYear="1996" baseAuthorityName="Hustedt" box="[655,1451,1720,1747]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Geissleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="3" pageNumber="252" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="acceptata">
<emphasis box="[655,887,1720,1746]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="252">Geissleria acceptata</emphasis>
(Hustedt) 
<bibRefCitation author="Lange-Bertalot, H. &amp; Metzeltin, D." box="[1009,1451,1720,1747]" pageId="3" pageNumber="252" pagination="1 - 390" refId="ref6930" refString="Lange-Bertalot, H. &amp; Metzeltin, D. (1996) Indicators of oligotrophy - 800 taxa representative of three ecologically distinct lake types, Carbonate buffered - Oligodystrophic - Weakly buffered soft water. Iconographia Diatomologica 2: 1 - 390." type="journal article" year="1996">Lange-Bertalot &amp; Metzeltin (1996: 64)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
but differs by rather large valves and more elliptical valves (not linear-elliptical). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lange-Bertalot &amp; Metzeltin" authorityYear="1996" baseAuthorityName="Hustedt" box="[1062,1206,1756,1782]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Geissleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="3" pageNumber="252" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="acceptata">
<emphasis box="[1062,1206,1756,1782]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="252">G. acceptata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
possesses an isolated pore, a structure that is absent in 
<taxonomicName authority="Kulikovskiy &amp; Gusev &amp; Andreeva &amp; Annenkova, 2014" authorityName="Kulikovskiy &amp; Gusev &amp; Andreeva &amp; Annenkova" authorityYear="2014" box="[512,685,1792,1818]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Geissleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="3" pageNumber="252" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="frolikhiensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[512,685,1792,1818]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="252">G. frolikhiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[693,780,1793,1819]" pageId="3" pageNumber="252" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Novais, M. H. &amp; Wetzel, C. E. &amp; Van de Vijver, B. &amp; Morais, M. M. &amp; Hoffmann, L. &amp; Ector L." box="[795,1010,1792,1818]" pageId="3" pageNumber="252" pagination="117 - 148" refId="ref7094" refString="Novais, M. H., Wetzel, C. E., Van de Vijver, B., Morais, M. M., Hoffmann, L. &amp; Ector L. (2013) New species and combinations in the genus Geissleria (Bacilllariophyceae). Cryptogamie, Algologie 34 (2): 117 - 148. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.7872 / crya. v 34. iss 2.2013.117" type="journal article" year="2013">
Novais 
<emphasis box="[884,942,1792,1818]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="252">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
). Other similar species are absent from Europe or elsewhere (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Lange-Bertalot, H." box="[437,675,1828,1854]" pageId="3" pageNumber="252" pagination="1 - 526" refId="ref6900" refString="Lange-Bertalot, H. (2001) Navicula sensu stricto. 10 genera separated from Navicula sensu lato, Frustulia. Diatom of Europe 2: 1 - 526." type="journal article" year="2001">Lange-Bertalot 2001</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Novais, M. H. &amp; Wetzel, C. E. &amp; Van de Vijver, B. &amp; Morais, M. M. &amp; Hoffmann, L. &amp; Ector L." box="[689,908,1828,1854]" pageId="3" pageNumber="252" pagination="117 - 148" refId="ref7094" refString="Novais, M. H., Wetzel, C. E., Van de Vijver, B., Morais, M. M., Hoffmann, L. &amp; Ector L. (2013) New species and combinations in the genus Geissleria (Bacilllariophyceae). Cryptogamie, Algologie 34 (2): 117 - 148. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.7872 / crya. v 34. iss 2.2013.117" type="journal article" year="2013">
Novais 
<emphasis box="[778,838,1828,1854]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="252">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="Kulikovskiy, Lange-Bertalot &amp; Metzeltin (2012: 117)" authorityName="Kulikovskiy, Lange-Bertalot &amp; Metzeltin" authorityPageNumber="117" authorityYear="2012" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Geissleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="3" pageNumber="252" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="irregularis">
<emphasis box="[929,1086,1828,1854]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="252">G. irregularis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kulikovskiy, M. S. &amp; Lange-Bertalot, H. &amp; Metzeltin, D. &amp; Witkowski, A." pageId="3" pageNumber="252" pagination="7 - 608" refId="ref6581" refString="Kulikovskiy, M. S., Lange-Bertalot, H., Metzeltin, D. &amp; Witkowski, A. (2012 a) Lake Baikal: hotspot of endemic diatoms I. Iconographia Diatomologica, V. 23, A. R. G. Gantner Verlag K. G., pp. 7 - 608." type="book chapter" year="2012">Kulikovskiy, Lange-Bertalot &amp; Metzeltin (2012: 117)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from Lake Baikal differs by asymmetrical valves to the apical axis, central area. No similar species are known from Lake Baikal.
</paragraph>
